# Design

This folder is the engineer-facing reference for {{PROJECT_NAME}}'s visual design. The
`designer` agent (see [`../agents/designer.md`](../agents/designer.md)) owns it: on UI/UX
tasks it produces per-task design briefs and self-contained HTML mockups, and it maintains
the design system here.

## Where things live

| Artifact | Location |
|---|---|
| **Product UI brief** (tone, surfaces, constraints) | [`../specs/ui-design-brief.md`](../specs/ui-design-brief.md) |
| **Per-task design** (surfaces, flows, states) | `../specs/<task>-design.md` (written by the designer agent) |
| **Visual mockups** (what screens look like) | Self-contained HTML under [`mockups/`](#mockups) — the primary, tool-independent visual artifact |
| **Design system** (tokens, components, motion, light/dark) | [`design-system.md`](./design-system.md) |
| **Decision log** (why we chose what) | Bottom of `design-system.md` |
| **External tool snapshots** (optional) | [`exports/`](#exports) |

## Workflow

1. The product-level brief in [`../specs/ui-design-brief.md`](../specs/ui-design-brief.md)
   sets tone and constraints.
2. For a UI/UX task, the **designer agent** reads the task spec and produces
   `../specs/<task>-design.md` plus HTML mockups under `mockups/<task-slug>/`. The mockups
   are the source of truth for what the screens look like — plain HTML + inline CSS, no
   external tool required.
3. System-level decisions (tokens, type scale, shared components, motion) are distilled
   into [`design-system.md`](./design-system.md). This is what engineers consume when
   implementing.
4. Each load-bearing visual decision (e.g. "stacked-bar over donut for daily breakdown")
   is logged in the Decision Log at the bottom of `design-system.md`, not duplicated
   elsewhere.

## Mockups

Self-contained HTML mockups from the designer agent live under `mockups/`, one folder per
task:

```
mockups/
└── <task-slug>/
    ├── home.html          ← standalone HTML + inline CSS, opens in any browser
    ├── entry-detail.html
    └── empty-state.html
```

Each file is framework-agnostic and dependency-free — a visual reference the developer
translates into the real stack, not implementation code.

## Exports

If you *also* iterate in an external design tool (Figma / Stitch / Whimsical / etc.),
periodic snapshots live under `exports/`. Each iteration gets its own dated folder; nothing
is overwritten.

```
exports/
└── <tool>-YYYY-MM-DD/
    ├── <screen_name>/
    │   ├── code.html      ← HTML/CSS rendering, if the tool exports it
    │   └── screen.png     ← static reference image
    └── ...
```

The dated folder name makes it easy to talk about "the 2026-05-02 export" and to keep older
snapshots around for comparison.
